Residential

Important
Notice

   E-mails, texts and voice phishing

   Phishing emails and texts are currently in circulation. Do not click on
   any hyperlinks they may contain. Also, Hydro‑Québec never uses these
   means of communication to ask for payment by credit card or to issue a
   reimbursement. If you receive such a message, inform your local
   police force.

I want to

     * Sign up for Online Billing
     * See my Consumption profile
     * Sign up for the Equalized Payments Plan
     * Report a change of address
     * Become a customer

Promotions

     * Need a new water heater? Get a $100 instant rebate when you buy a
       water heater with ECOPEAK® technology.
     * Thank heavens for Online Billing! Available anywhere, anytime.
     * Do you know which wires are dangerous? This short video will
       show you.

Important
Notice

   E-mails, texts and voice phishing

   Phishing emails and texts are currently in circulation. Do not click on
   any hyperlinks they may contain. Also, Hydro‑Québec never uses these
   means of communication to ask for payment by credit card or to issue a
   reimbursement. If you receive such a message, inform your local
   police force.

Online services
without waiting

Options in case of payment difficulties

   On a tight budget right now? Don’t think you can pay your bill on time?
   We can come up with a solution.

Track a request for work

   Is your request in progress, complete or pending? Track the the status
   of your request anytime, anywhere. The information is at your
   fingertips!

Power outage info

   Is there an outage in your area? You can find out how big an area is
   affected and when service will be restored.

   View all our services

Guides to help you make the right choices

Are you interested in installing solar panels?

   See our Web site to learn more about PV solar power before you invest.

Guided tours

   Discover feats of Québec engineering by visiting Hydro-Québec
   facilities. School groups are welcome.

Safety reminders

   Learn to recognize the electrical hazards of power lines, trees and
   poles, as well as in and around the house!

